               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#add-summary">
                     1 copy of Dabistān by Fānī, Muḥsin -1671 or 1672
                  </summary>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_190-item1">
                     <author key="person_47114320" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/47114320">
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Fānī, Muḥsin -1671 or 1672</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">Mullā Muḥammad Amīn</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar">ملا محمد امین</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_2250">Dabistān</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt" key="work_2250">Dabistān-i maz̲āhib min taṣnīf-i Mullā Muḥammad</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_2250">دبستان</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" type="alt" key="work_2250">دبستان المذاهب من تصنیف ملا محمد امین</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" type="alt" key="work_2250">Dabistān al-maẕāhib</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" type="alt" key="work_2250">Dabistān-i maẕāhib</title>
                     <colophon>The title of the manuscript and the name of the author are given in the colophon, on f. <locus from="265v" to="265v">265v</locus>, as being Dabistān-i Maz̲āhib by Mullā Muḥammad Amīn, copied by Zu al-Fiqār ‘Alī on Wednesday 22nd Safar: بتاریخ بیست و دویم شهر صفر المظفر بروز چهارشنبه بوقت عصر بدستخط ذوالفقار علیصورت اتمام پذیرفت…. نسخه دبستان مذاهب من تصنیف ملا محمد امین</colophon>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa" type="basmalla">بسم الله الرحمان ای نام تو سر دفتر اطفال دبستان یاد تو ببالغ نظران شمع شبستان</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar"/>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>In the subscription of another copy of this work in British Museum (Rieu, BM 141a- 142b) the authorship is ascribed to Mullā Muḥammad Amīn, and Zu al-Fiqār ‘Alī, to whom this work is also ascribed, is only the copyist (see <idno>MS Persian 075</idno>, <idno>MS Persian 189</idno>, <idno>MS Persian 190</idno> and Rieu, BM 142b-143a).</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
